 beelta bit uneasy.
  I was in a place I didn't know, with people I didn't know. I didn't know what was going to happen to me.

"Excuse me," I said to him.
 "Can you tell me where I am?" "You're in the cinema," he said.
 "You died, and now you're watching your next life." "But what is this place?
" I said. "Is it a world-between-worlds?" 
"o," he said.
 "This is the cinema."  Finding him very useless, I approached the woman next to him. 
Excuse me," I said to her.
  "Where am I?" 
You're in the cinema," she said.

"o," he said.

Excuse me," I said to her.
  "Where am I?" 
You're in the cinema," she said.

I looked around for someone to ask. I saw a man who looked like me. He had similar clothes, gender, hair, and seemed to be from a more recent era. Many of the people had older clothing, from the 50s, 60s, 70s, and 80s, but his outfit looked modern. 
"Excuse me," I said to him.
 "Can you tell me where I am?" "You're in the cinema," he said.
 "You died, and now you're watching your next life." "But what is this place?
" I said. "Is it a world-between-worlds?" 
"o," he said.
 "This is the cinema."  Finding him very useless, I approached the woman next to him. 
Excuse me," I said to her.
  "Where am I?" 
You're in the cinema," she said.
 

Nobody I asked was able to answer my questions, and indeed, the whole theater stared like zombies at the screen, waiting for the show to begin.  I suddenly noticed a female version of myself, quietly beckoning me over.  She put finger to her lips, and pointed to one of the stage doors, off to the side. Intrigued, I began to head toward her.  Suddenly, I heard a loud gruff voice behind me. "Stop! Don't let the anomaly escape!" 
I turned around, and saw a man in a suit, with a badge that said "Security". Frightened, I bolted to the door. The woman closed the the door, and leaned against it. "Run!", she said. "run to the forest, or they will take you!" I ran as fast as I could, and I didn't look back.

I began to wonder where I was at. "What exactly is this place?", I wondered. "Am I in a world-between-worlds?" 
 beelta bit uneasy.
  I was in a place I didn't know, with people I didn't know. I didn't know what was going to happen to me.

I looked around for someone to ask. I saw a man who looked like me. He had similar clothes, gender, hair, and seemed to be from a more recent era. Many of the people had older clothing, from the 50s, 60s, 70s, and 80s, but his outfit looked modern. 
"Excuse me," I said to him.
 "Can you tell me where I am?" "You're in the cinema," he said.
 "You died, and now you're watching your next life." "But what is this place?
" I said. "Is it a world-between-worlds?" 
"o," he said.
 "This is the cinema."  Finding him very useless, I approached the woman next to him. 
Excuse me," I said to her.
  "Where am I?" 
You're in the cinema," she said.
 

Nobody I asked was able to answer my questions, and indeed, the whole theater stared like zombies at the screen, waiting for the show to begin.  I suddenly noticed a female version of myself, quietly beckoning me over.  She put finger to her lips, and pointed to one of the stage doors, off to the side. Intrigued, I began to head toward her.  Suddenly, I heard a loud gruff voice behind me. "Stop! Don't let the anomaly escape!" 
I turned around, and saw a man in a suit, with a badge that said "Security". Frightened, I bolted to the door. The woman closed the the door, and leaned against it. "Run!", she said. "run to the forest, or they will take you!" I ran as fast as I could, and I didn't look back.

I looked around for someone to ask. I saw a man who looked like me. He had similar clothes, gender, hair, and seemed to be from a more recent era. Many of the people had older clothing, from the 50s, 60s, 70s, and 80s, but his outfit looked modern. 
"Excuse me," I said to him.
 "Can you tell me where I am?" "You're in the cinema," he said.
 "You died, and now you're watching your next life." "But what is this place?
" I said. "Is it a world-between-worlds?" 
"o," he said.
 "This is the cinema."  Finding him very useless, I approached the woman next to him. 
Excuse me," I said to her.
  "Where am I?" 
You're in the cinema," she said.
 

Nobody I asked was able to answer my questions, and indeed, the whole theater stared like zombies at the screen, waiting for the show to begin.  I suddenly noticed a female version of myself, quietly beckoning me over.  She put finger to her lips, and pointed to one of the stage doors, off to the side. Intrigued, I began to head toward her.  Suddenly, I heard a loud gruff voice behind me. "Stop! Don't let the anomaly escape!" 
I turned around, and saw a man in a suit, with a badge that said "Security". Frightened, I bolted to the door. The woman closed the the door, and leaned against it. "Run!", she said. "run to the forest, or they will take you!" I ran as fast as I could, and I didn't look back.

 "Can you tell me where I am?" "You're in the cinema," he said.
 "You died, and now you're watching your next life." "But what is this place?

"o," he said.

Excuse me," I said to her.

You're in the cinema," she said.

 "Can you tell me where I am?" "You're in the cinema," he said.
 "You died, and now you're watching your next life." "But what is this place?
" I said. "Is it a world-between-worlds?" 
"o," he said.
 "This is the cinema."  Finding him very useless, I approached the woman next to him. 
Excuse me," I said to her.
  "Where am I?" 
You're in the cinema," she said.
 

Nobody I asked was able to answer my questions, and indeed, the whole theater stared like zombies at the screen, waiting for the show to begin.  I suddenly noticed a female version of myself, quietly beckoning me over.  She put finger to her lips, and pointed to one of the stage doors, off to the side. Intrigued, I began to head toward her.  Suddenly, I heard a loud gruff voice behind me. "Stop! Don't let the anomaly escape!" 
I turned around, and saw a man in a suit, with a badge that said "Security". Frightened, I bolted to the door. The woman closed the the door, and leaned against it. "Run!", she said. "run to the forest, or they will take you!" I ran as fast as I could, and I didn't look back.
